Support Vector Regression => 

Simple linear regression is just a line through the dataset and to find the line that 
best fits, we use the ordinary least squares(SUM(y - yhat) -> minimum)
minimise the distance between predicted value y and the actual value in the dataset


SVregression, instead of a simple line, see a tube, with a regression line in the middle 
the tube has a width of episolun as measured vertically. this means any point that falls 
inside the tube will be disregarding the error, inside the tube dont care abt the error line 
between the predicted value and the actual value because it falls inside the tube or the 
episolun. so thats key behind support vector regression. 
gives the model a buffer
points outside the episolun tube, and for them we do care about the error and will be 
measured as the distance between the pt and tube itself. 


